the other $emicircle E F D. The additions and $ubductions
in this place therefore, that is in the time of the $ol$tice, $hall be
mea$ured by the whole diameter D E.</P>
<P>Let us in the next place enquire, Whether they be of the $ame
bigne$s in the times of the <I>E</I>quinoxes; and tran$porting the
Centre of the Earth to the point I, di$tant a Quadrant of a
