with me prai$e and admire the Wi$dome and Greatne$$e of the
Creator, which I di$cover to him by a more narrow explication
of the Worlds Form, the Di$qui$ition of Cau$es, and Detection
<foot>of</foot>
<p n=>467</p>
of the Errours of Sight: And $o he will not onely extoll the
Bounty of God in the pre$ervation of Living Creatures of all
kindes, and e$tabli$hment of the Earth; but even in its Motion
