$ure; and if they decrea$e in velocity, they increa$e in mea-
$ure.</P>
<P>Secondly, I con$ider that the mea$ures of tho$e Brooks and
Rivers, which enter into <I>Tiber</I> at the time of Innundation, are
not between them$elves really the $ame, when their velocities are
