and by this means we $hall avoid the di$order hinted in the
$eventh Appendix. It would be nece$$ary neverthele$s, to ac-
commodate the Cocks of the Ci$tern $o, that the level of the
water in the Ci$tern may alwayes re$t at one determinate mark
above the Cock, otherwi$e the Cocks will emit $ometimes
greater, and $ometimes le$$e abundance of water: And becau$e
it may be that the $ame water of the Fountain may be $ometimes
more abundant, $ometimes le$s; in $uch ca$e it will be nece$$ary
<foot>to</foot>
<p n=>23</p>
to adju$t the Ci$tern $o, that the exce$s above the ordinary wa-
