<p n=>76</p>
clare and prote$t that there $hall follow very great dammages
to the Fields of the main Land, and extraordinary $ummes
$hall be expended to no purpo$e. The Lake undoubtedly will
become almo$t dry, and will prove impa$$ible for Navigation,
with a manife$t danger of corrupting the Air: And in the la$t
place there will unavoidably en$ue the choaking and $toppage of
the Ports of <I>Venice.</I></P>
<P>Upon the 20th. of <I>December,</I> 1641. I imparted this my $econd
Con$ideration to the mo$t Excellent <I>Signore Ba$adonna,</I> pre$en-
ting him with a Copy thereof among$t other Writings, which I
