<P>SAGREDUS.</P>
<P><I>Simplicius,</I> and I, $taid expecting your com-
ing, and we have been trying to recall to
memory our la$t Con$ideration, which, as
the Principle and Suppo$ition, on which
you ground the Conclu$ions that you in-
tended to Demon$trate to us, was that
Re$i$tance, that all Bodies have to <I>Fracti-
on,</I> depending on that Cement, that con-
nects and glutinates the parts, $o, as that
they do not $eparate and divide without a powerful attraction:
and our enquiry hath been, what might be the Cau$e of that
