<head>THEOR. II. PROP. II.</head>
<P>If a Moveable in equal Times pa$$e thorow two
Spaces, the $aid Spaces will be to each other,
as the Velocities. And if the Spaces are to each
other as the Velocities, the Times will be
equal.</P>
<P><I>Let us $uppo$e A B and B C in the former Figure, to be two
Spaces pa$t, by the Moveable in equal times; the Space A B with
the Velocity D E, and the Space B C with the Velocity E F. I
$ay, that the Space A B is to the Space B C, as the Velocity D E is to
