<head>THEOREM.</head>
<P><I>The degrees of Velocity of a Moveable de$cending with a Natural
Motion from the $ame height along Planes in any manner inclined
at the arrival to the Horizon are alwaies equal, Impediments be-
ing removed.</I></P>
<P>Here we are in the fir$t place to adverti$e you, that it having
been proved, that in any Inclination of the Plane the Move-
