<P>SAGR. Really me thinks that we may ju$tly grant our <I>Acade-
mian</I> what he without arrogance a$$umed to him$elf in the begining
of this his Treati$e of $hewing us a <I>New Science</I> about <I>a very old
Subject.</I> And to $ee with what Facility and Per$picuity he deduceth
from one $ole Principle the Demon$trations of $o many Propo$iti-
