may $ay, that never till now was the door opened to a new Con-
templation fraught with infinite and admirable Conclu$ions, which
in times to come may bu$ie other Wits.</P>
<P>SAGR. <I>I</I> verily believe, that as tho$e few Pa$$ions (<I>I</I> will $ay
for example) of the Circle demon$trated by <I>Euclid</I> in the third of
his <I>Elements</I> are an introduction to innumerable others more ab-
$truce, $o tho$e produced and demon$trated in this $hort Tractate,
when they $hall come to the hands of other Speculative Wits, $hall
