ring the</I> Impetus, <I>or the Moment of Velocity upon a Line along which it
makes a Motion of De$cent is therefore manife$t; which</I> Impetus
<I>is indeed $uppo$ed to encrea$e according to the Proportion of the
Time.</I></P>
<P><I>But this, before we proceed any farther, is to be premoni$hed, that in
regard we are to $peak for the future of the Motion compounded of the
