$uming another of the $ame kind. And that I may the better expre$s
my meaning; Let A C be Perpendicular to the Horizon C B; and A C</I>
<foot><I>to</I></foot>
<p n=>219</p>
<I>to be the Altitude, and C B the Amplitude of the Semiparabola A B;
which is de$cribed by the Compo$ition of two Lations; of which one is
that of the Moveable de$cending along A C with a Motion Naturally
