along the De$cent A C is determined by the quantity of the $aid height
A C; for the</I> Impetus <I>of a Moveable</I>
<fig>
<I>falling from the $ame height is alwaies
one and the $ame: but in the Horizontal
Line one may a$$ign not one, but innume-
rable Degrees of Velocities of Equable
Motions: out of which multitude that I
may $ingle out, and as it were point with
the finger to that which I make choice of,
I extend or prolong the Altitude C A</I> in
$ublimi, <I>in which, as was done before, I
will pitch upon A E; from which if I
conceive in my mind a Moveable to fall</I>
ex quiete <I>in E, it appeareth that its</I> Im-
petus <I>acquired in the Time A, is one with which I conceive the $ame
