<P><I>Let there be a Conoid who$e Axis is A B, and the Center of the
circum$cribed Figure C, and the Center of the in$cribed O. I $ay
the Center of the Conoid is betwixt the points C and O. For if
not, it $hall be either above them, or below them, or in one of them. Let
it be below, as in R. And becau$e R is the Center of Gravity of the
