<fig>
<I>Ba$e. That it falleth without, or in its
Ba$e it is already manife$t to be an ab$ur-
dity. Let it fall within: and becau$e X R
is to R O, as the in$cribed Figure is to
the exce$s by which the Conoid exceeds
it; the $ame proportion that B R hath to
R O, the $ame let the in$cribed Figure
