Wherefore, by Divi$ion, as H S is to S X, $o $hall the</I> Fru$tum <I>who$e</I>
<foot><I>Axis</I></foot>
<p n=>270</p>
<I>Axis is D V be to the Cone or Pyramid who$e Axis is V A. And as
H S is to S X, $o al$o is M D to O N. Wherefore the</I> Fru$tum <I>is to the
Pyramid who$e Axis is A V, as M D to N O. And becau$e A N
is 3/4 of A D; and A I is 3/4 of A V; the remainder I N $hall be 3/4 of the
